abstract: ST. PETERSBURG, Feb. 9. The Russian Telegraphic Agency states that the dispatch of the British fleet to the Bosphorus restores to Russia liberty of action. If the object is to co-operate in the maintenance of order and the attainment of a durable and equitable solution of the Eastern question, the fleet will be welcomed as an auxiliary. At any rate, Russia will regulate her attitude by that of England.

abstract: The wooden, screw steam-ship City of Dallas, of Mallory's coast-line, was almost destroyed by fire last night, and her freight--a half-cargo of cotton, oranges, and ship-stores--was completely ruined by flames and water. The loss occasioned is about $75,000. The origin of the fire is unknown. Suggestions of spontaneous combustion were made during the conflagration, but upon what ground they were based did not appear very clearly.
